    <sys:String x:Key="About_Description">This app helps you manage visitors, authors, books, and publishers for a book fair. You can add new records, review existing ones, and sort data.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_AuthorsHeader">Authors:</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author1">Ivo Andrić – Nobel Prize winner and one of the most famous Serbian writers. His works often explore history and everyday life in Bosnia.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author2">Fredrik Backman – Swedish author known for warm, humorous novels that blend comedy with empathy.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author3">Antoine de Saint-Exupéry – French writer and pilot, best known for The Little Prince, a world classic.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author4">Markus Zusak – Australian author best known for The Book Thief.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author5">Agatha Christie – English crime novelist famous for suspenseful mysteries and plot twists.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author6">Harper Lee – American author best known for To Kill a Mockingbird.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author7">Ernest Hemingway – American novelist and Nobel Prize winner known for a clear, direct style.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author8">Arthur Conan Doyle – Creator of Sherlock Holmes and master of detective stories.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author9">Fyodor Dostoevsky – Russian novelist who explored morality, psychology, and existential dilemmas.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author10">Emily Brontë – English novelist, author of Wuthering Heights.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author11">Terry Pratchett – British fantasy author known for the Discworld series.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="About_Author12">Neil Gaiman – English author of fantasy and comics, known for dark, magical storytelling.</sys:String>

